description:
In 74ed20c (develop/7) when I use this query:
PREFIX s: <http://schema.org/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
CONSTRUCT {
 ?b s:geo ?c ;
      s:title ?title;
      s:description ?desc ;
      <http://linked.opendata.cz/ontology/domain/seznam.gov.cz/ovm/typSubjektu> ?type.
?type skos:prefLabel ?typeText ;
          ?p ?o .
?c s:latitude ?lat; s:longitude ?lng .
} WHERE {
 ?b s:name ?title ;
      <http://linked.opendata.cz/ontology/domain/seznam.gov.cz/ovm/typSubjektu> ?type ;
      s:address ?address .
?address s:streetAddress ?street;
      s:postalCode ?psc;
      s:addressRegion ?region;
      s:addressLocality ?locality.
?type skos:prefLabel ?typeText ;
          ?p ?o .
graph <http://linked.opendata.cz/resource/dataset/geocoordinates/google/schema.org> {
          ?c s:longitude ?lng;
              s:latitude ?lat ;
              ^s:geo ?address.
}
BIND(concat(?typeText, ": ", ?title, """
""",?street, """
""", ?region ,"""
""", ?locality, """
""", ?psc ) as ?desc)
}
it takes forever to answer.
When I omit the ?p and ?o variables, the query evaluates within seconds:
PREFIX s: <http://schema.org/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
CONSTRUCT {
 ?b s:geo ?c ;
      s:title ?title;
      s:description ?desc ;
      <http://linked.opendata.cz/ontology/domain/seznam.gov.cz/ovm/typSubjektu> ?type.
?type skos:prefLabel ?typeText .
?c s:latitude ?lat; s:longitude ?lng .
} WHERE {
 ?b s:name ?title ;
      <http://linked.opendata.cz/ontology/domain/seznam.gov.cz/ovm/typSubjektu> ?type ;
      s:address ?address .
?address s:streetAddress ?street;
      s:postalCode ?psc;
      s:addressRegion ?region;
      s:addressLocality ?locality.
?type skos:prefLabel ?typeText .
graph <http://linked.opendata.cz/resource/dataset/geocoordinates/google/schema.org> {
          ?c s:longitude ?lng;
              s:latitude ?lat ;
              ^s:geo ?address.
}
BIND(concat(?typeText, ": ", ?title, """
""",?street, """
""", ?region ,"""
""", ?locality, """
""", ?psc ) as ?desc)
}
Each of the ?type skos:Concepts has approx. 3 more triples that would be returned by the ?p and ?o variables.
In addition, it seems that even adding just one more property like this causes this performance issue:
PREFIX s: <http://schema.org/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
CONSTRUCT {
 ?b s:geo ?c ;
      s:title ?title;
      s:description ?desc ;
      <http://linked.opendata.cz/ontology/domain/seznam.gov.cz/ovm/typSubjektu> ?type;
      <http://linked.opendata.cz/ontology/domain/seznam.gov.cz/ovm/datumOvereni> ?datum .
?type skos:prefLabel ?typeText .
?c s:latitude ?lat; s:longitude ?lng .
} WHERE {
 ?b s:name ?title ;
      <http://linked.opendata.cz/ontology/domain/seznam.gov.cz/ovm/typSubjektu> ?type ;
      <http://linked.opendata.cz/ontology/domain/seznam.gov.cz/ovm/datumOvereni> ?datum ;
      s:address ?address .
?address s:streetAddress ?street;
      s:postalCode ?psc;
      s:addressRegion ?region;
      s:addressLocality ?locality.
?type skos:prefLabel ?typeText .
graph <http://linked.opendata.cz/resource/dataset/geocoordinates/google/schema.org> {
          ?c s:longitude ?lng;
              s:latitude ?lat ;
              ^s:geo ?address.
}
BIND(concat(?typeText, ": ", ?title, """
""",?street, """
""", ?region ,"""
""", ?locality, """
""", ?psc ) as ?desc)
}
